projects:
[{'title': 'DSHBA', 'date': {'start': {'month': 10, 'day': None, 'year': 2020}, 'end': {'month': 1, 'day': None, 'year': 2021}}, 'description': 'Highly optimized emulator for the Nintendo GameBoy Advance (GBA). Written in C++20, with good compatibility for most GBA games and homebrew. Faster even that most GBA emulators I know (even some that are known for being extremely performant). I wrote a hardware renderer for it, that does all rendering entirely on the GPU (requires OpenGL 3.3). Other optimizations are described in the README of the linked GitHub profile. Later on I turned the CPU interpreter into a "cached interpreter", and I wrote a little bit about it here:
https://densinh.github.io/DenSinH/emulation/optimizations/2021/01/31/cached-interpreter.html
also published on emudev.org at:
https://emudev.org/2021/01/31/cached-interpreter.html', 'contributors': [{'type': 'standardizedContributor', 'first_name': 'Dennis', 'last_name': 'Hilhorst', 'name': None, 'headline': 'My name is Dennis Hilhorst. I am a third year student at Utrecht University, where I study mathematics and physics.'}]}, {'title': 'GameBoy Advance Replacement BIOS', 'date': {'start': {'month': 7, 'day': None, 'year': 2020}, 'end': {'month': 11, 'day': None, 'year': 2020}}, 'description': 'Open source, replacement BIOS for the Nintendo GameBoy Advance. Written entirely in ARMv4t assembly, together with a fellow emulator developer. Required disassembling of some BIOS functions, and reimplementing them in a more optimized way.', 'contributors': [{'type': 'standardizedContributor', 'first_name': 'Dennis', 'last_name': 'Hilhorst', 'name': None, 'headline': 'My name is Dennis Hilhorst. Written partly in ARMv4t assembly and partly in Python. Allows the user to generate test ROMs that check a randomly generated input versus an expected outcome. Can test both ARM and THUMB mode instructions, in the data processing, load/store and multiplication categories.', 'contributors': [{'type': 'standardizedContributor', 'first_name': 'Dennis', 'last_name': 'Hilhorst', 'name': None, 'headline': 'My name is Dennis Hilhorst. I am a third year student at Utrecht University, where I study mathematics and physics.'}]}, {'title': 'AGS Aging Cartridge Test Decompilation', 'date': {'start': {'month': None, 'day': None, 'year': None}, 'end': {'month': None, 'day': None, 'year': None}}, 'description': 'Reverse engineered all the (enabled) tests in the Nintendo AGS Aging Cartridge test ROM for the GameBoy Advance, and wrote their workings out in C. I also described the tests workings, and what the output is.
